comment: If for every element of a finite indexing set ` A ` there exists a corresponding element of another set ` B ` , then there exists a finite subset of ` B ` consisting only of those elements which are indexed by ` A ` . Proven without the Axiom of Choice, unlike ~ indexdom . (Contributed by Jeff Madsen, 2-Sep-2009.) (Proof shortened by Mario Carneiro, 12-Sep-2015.)
